cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use logos, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "logos: a falsifiable, decontaminated inference framework for testing undeciphered-script decipherment claims"
abstract: >-
  logos is a discipline harness for telling a real decipherment of an undeciphered script from a fitted
  one: pre-registered predictions, multiple-testing deflation (effective-n, deflated significance),
  contamination control (a literature index with an L_known/L_virgin partition, LLM-ablation, and an
  L_fake fabricated-corpus canary), and a held-out graduation gate computed mechanically. Linear A is
  the worked null: a body of rigorous, pre-registered negative results bounded by the corpus's
  information floor.
type: software
